<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-09-18T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-09-18T16:00:00-05:00" n="721" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d721">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.50 Am 3/17: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Houghton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-18T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September 18,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>122. Your 187, September 16, 4 p.m. A public announcement is being made
                            that in view of Soviet refusal matter is now considered to be
                            terminated.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>